Taiwan Stock Movers: Advanced Semiconductor, HTC Corp., Silitech

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-12-07T01:39:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/taiwan-stock-movers-advanced-semiconductor-htc-corp-silitech.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual (TWSE)  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are at 9:38 a.m. in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 0.8 percent to 7,012.70, set for the
first advance in four days.  Advanced Semiconductor Engineering Inc. (2311)  (2311 TT) increased
1.5 percent to NT$27.95. Unit ASE Test Inc. plans to invest $60
million in ASE (Kunshan) Inc. in China, Advanced Semiconductor
said in a statement to the local stock exchange yesterday.  HTC Corp. (2498 TT) lost 1 percent to NT$453.50. November
sales dropped 18 percent from a year earlier to NT$30.8 billion
from a year earlier, the company reported to the exchange.  Silitech Technology Corp. (3311)  (3311 TT) advanced 2.1 percent to
NT$76.60. November sales rose 19 percent from a year earlier to
NT$619.6 million, the company said in a statement to the  Taiwan
Stock Exchange  yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
